  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<h2></b>Description</b></h2></p><p>This drab brown, hooded cloak acts as a cloak of resistance +1 but also quickly absorbs any liquids poured onto it, drying in moments. Three times per day, the wearer can pour a vial of holy water onto the interior lining of an aspergillum cloak, causing its outer surface to glisten and drip. The holy water cannot be recovered once absorbed. For 7 minutes, the garment is soaked in holy water, dealing 2d4 points of damage to any undead or evil outsider that strikes the wearer with an unarmed strike or a natural weapon. An aspergillum cloak can also absorb unholy water instead, dealing damage to good outsiders instead. An aspergillum cloak gains no special abilities from absorbing any other liquid.<br><p><b>Base Item:</b> </p><h3><b>Requirements</b></h3><p>Craft Wondrous Item, bless water</p><h3><b>Source: </b></h3>Black Markets",
